com.giannoules.proxstor.api

Class Locality

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.giannoules.proxstor.api.Locality

  • public class Locality
extends Object
    ProxStor representation of an locality. An locality is the vertex created whenever a user "checks-in" to a location. The association is tracked in this object, which captures: - user - location - device (if not manual mode) - environmental sensed (if not manual mode) - whether the check in was manual - whether the user is actively in the location - date/time of arrival - date/time of departure This class is augmented with annotations identifying it for Java Architecture for XML Binding.
    Author:
    James Giannoules
